From: Liu Ying <Ying.Liu@freescale.com>
Date: Tue, 29 Oct 2013 11:26:40 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 0599/1072] ENGR00285273-1 IPU dev:Correct timeout setting
 from users

git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-2.6-imx.git imx_3.10.17_1.0.0_beta
commit 3d8f745c5d554850c3c5054af1955d3aa92413bf

This patch corrects the logic to set timeout value specified
by the users.

Signed-off-by: Liu Ying <Ying.Liu@freescale.com>
Signed-off-by: Hongbo Zhong <hongbo.zhong@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/mxc/ipu3/ipu_device.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mxc/ipu3/ipu_device.c b/drivers/mxc/ipu3/ipu_device.c
index 6781582..1df0005 100644
--- a/drivers/mxc/ipu3/ipu_device.c
+++ b/drivers/mxc/ipu3/ipu_device.c
@@ -1403,7 +1403,7 @@ static struct ipu_task_entry *create_task_entry(struct ipu_task *task)
 	tsk->overlay_en = task->overlay_en;
 	if (tsk->overlay_en)
 		tsk->overlay = task->overlay;
-	if (tsk->timeout && (tsk->timeout > DEF_TIMEOUT_MS))
+	if (task->timeout > DEF_TIMEOUT_MS)
 		tsk->timeout = task->timeout;
 	else
 		tsk->timeout = DEF_TIMEOUT_MS;
